Java Servlets and JavaServer Pages (JSP) are foundational server-side technologies in Java used to build dynamic web applications. 
While both handle HTTP requests and responses, Servlets focus on backend business logic while JSP simplifies frontend UI presentation.

Servlets are .java files returning response in HTML format. Executed in the Web browser
JSP are .jsp files written like HTML codes with Java embedded in it. These render servlet to be executed in the Web browser.



Apache Tomcat is an open-source web server and servlet container that executes Java Servlets and renders JavaServer Pages (JSP). 
It is widely used to host Java-based web applications and microservices (like Spring Boot) because of its lightweight, flexible, and robust nature.

